  "_comment_scenario": "Private Foundation Beneficial Ownership — Liechtenstein Privatstiftung with Founder, Foundation Council and Named Beneficiaries. This example demonstrates AMLR Art. 26(2)(c) disclosure for a foundation structure where Steinberg Asset Management AG (Switzerland) — the subject VASP entity — is 100% owned by the Steinberg Privatstiftung (Liechtenstein). Liechtenstein private foundations (Privatstiftung under PGR Art. 552 §§1–41) are a common wealth-structuring vehicle but present high opacity risk. FATF Recommendation 25 and AMLR Art. 26(2)(c) require identification of: [Founder] Heinrich Steinberg (DE) — settled assets into the foundation and, under the foundation statutes, retains reserved powers including the right to appoint and dismiss foundation council members and to amend the foundation purpose; [Foundation Council] Dr. Andreas Mayer LI (Chairman), Dr. Helga Kirchner DE, Marco Bergomi CH — three natural persons who constitute the governing body, documented via LPID mandates; [Beneficiaries] Heinrich Steinberg and his lineal descendants — identified in the foundation statutes and a supplementary beneficiary declaration. UBO determination: Heinrich Steinberg is the UBO because (i) as founder he retains statutory appointment/dismissal powers over the foundation council under PGR Art. 552 §29, giving him DE_FACTO_CONTROL, and (ii) he and his family are the exclusive beneficiaries. The foundation's charter has been obtained, reviewed and retained on the EDD file.",
